I would recommend using something like lodash&#39;s [debounce()][1] function in order to wait until the user has (probably) finished typing before redirecting. Vue actually has a great example of this in their docs on [watchers][2].

If you decide to include lodash in your project (it may already be included), you could do something like the following:

```
created() {
  this.debouncedSearch = _.debounce(this.search, 500)
},
methods: {
  search (term) {
    axios.get(`https://api.com/search?search=${term}`)
      .then(res =&gt; (this.results = res.data))
    }
  }
},
watch: {
  search: function(term) {
    this.debouncedSearch();
  }
}
```
Your search page would probably need its own search form/input in order to allow the user to continue to refine their search after being redirected to the search page.

  [1]: https://lodash.com/docs#debounce
  [2]: https://vuejs.org/v2/guide/computed.html#Watchers

